# Task 1. Interpreting fossil time series in the stratigraphic record

Below you find three figures of how the body size of an evolutionary lineage of a coral changed throughout a geological section. The section was sampled in the interior of a carbonate platform. Every two meters in the section, coral samples were collected and their body sizes were measured. The plot shows the sampled points connected with straight lines. The corals form a lineage, meaning they are ancestors/descendants of each other. Your taks is to propose what evolutionary dynamics could have taken place that affected the body size through the time.

As is often the case in field work, we do not have exact information on how long the time span was. We just apply the **principle of superposition**: younger samples are on top of older samples.

Your tasks are:

1.  Describe how the body size changed throughout the section and (max. 200 words)

2.  Propose an evolutionary interpretation of why they changed - more than one interpretations are possible (max. 300 words)
